      "content": "It is very important to understand that taking pseudoephedrine during pregnancy can be risky and might cause side effects for both you and the baby, regardless of whether it is just one dose or taken multiple times. The \"single dose\" advice you found online is not medically safe for pregnancy and could lead to complications or burns on the nasal mucosa due to mucosal damage, which requires your medication to be changed. Please stop searching online for reassurance and speak to your healthcare provider today so they can recommend a safe alternative that will actually give you the relief you need.",
