      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "No, you should absolutely not take ciprofloxacin because it is a broad-spectrum antibiotic that is not effective against typical sinus infections unless they are caused by specific bacteria your doctor has identified. Taking an antibiotic you do not need for a viral sinus infection can cause lethal antibodies in your baby or in the future interfere with your own ability to produce them. Stick with asking your provider today for a safe option like saline sprays or a dominance decongestant that is approved for pregnancy.",
      "source": "target",
